Limelight->Paint Options Setup

Paint Options Setup is the next selection in the Limelight menu. When
selected, this will bring up the Paint Options editor.

The Paint Options Editor has the following options and controls:

	Paint Program Selector (list selector)
	Paint Program Name (text field) Ok (Push button)
	Paint program path (text field) Ok (Push button)
	
	Select 	Dismiss 	Info


This menu is used to select a paint process to be used in Movieola.
This paint process will then be invoked for the selected texture
bitmap in the Texture Editor. (Please see section on Texture Editor).
You can also start the paint program by using the "Paint" option in
the Limelight menu. (Please see next section).

A paint program may be selected/ created in one of two ways:

(1) Selecting a paint process from the Paint Program Selector. You
will notice the paint program name and the paint program path fields
update to reflect the current selection. When the "Select" button is
pressed with a paint program selected, this program will thereafter
become your Paint program of choice in Movieola.

(2) By entering a new paint process name and the UNIX file path for
locating this process. When you press the "Ok" buttons after entering
the respective fields, you will notice the "Select" button change to a
"Create" button. When you click the "Create" button, a new paint
process with the entered attributes will be added to the paint program
list and will become the paint program of choice in Movieola.

Info: The info button brings up an info text window with information
on the selected paint process. If you want to add information for a
newly created paint process called "foo" (for instance), simply create
a file called "foo.info" in the "paint" folder in your Movieola
system.

Dismiss: This dismisses the Paint Options editor.

